description:
The contest that started between Jehovah and Pharaoh culminated in a seemingly impossible mission for Israel – crossing the Red Sea. Can the place where Israel faced this challenge be identified? In this lecture, Francois du Plessis does some exploring, and with the help of the Bible account, aerial images, and Josephus, he identifies Pi-Hahiroth, the place where Israel came to the Red Sea. 

What happened in this place? What lessons does the story of crossing the Red Sea have for God’s people living in the last days? Don’t miss out on this exciting story of God’s power to rescue His people.
